   "body" : "**This PR is a DRAFT**\r\n\r\nRationale: improve `importdescriptors` command\r\n\r\nCurrently if you run same `importdescriptors` command twice with a descriptor containing private key you will get very confusing error âÂ `Missing required fields`. What happens is that Wallet tries to write imported private key to the disk, but it exists already so we get `DB_KEYEXIST (-30995)` from BerkelyDB. Please note, that we set `DB_NOOVERWRITE` (I guess not to lose some keys accidentally). The exception is caught in `catch (...)` in rpcdump.cpp with a generic error.\r\n\r\nI modified `wallet_importdescriptors` test to reproduce the issue.\r\n\r\nI can see three possible solutions:\r\n1. *Implemented in this PR*. Just add keys to `new_spk_man` without dumping them to the disk. This is the simplest fix I could come up with, but I don't like code duplication with `DescriptorScriptPubKeyMan::AddDescriptorKey`\r\n2. Do not create new SPK manager and just update existing one in case imported descriptor already exists in the wallet.\r\n3. Allow to override records in BDB.\r\n\r\n",
